    slug: "tajweed-quran-color-coded",
    description: `Tajweed Quran — Color Coded is a specially formatted edition of the Holy Quran designed to assist readers in applying the rules of tajweed, the science of proper Quranic recitation. The entire text of the Quran has been marked with a sophisticated color-coding system that visually indicates the specific tajweed rules that apply to each letter and word, making it significantly easier for readers to identify and apply the correct pronunciation, elongation, nasalization, and articulation points required for beautiful and accurate recitation. This edition is based on the Hafs narration from Asim, which is the most widely used recitation style in the Muslim world.

The color-coding system uses distinct colors to represent the major categories of tajweed rules. The rules for the noon sakinah and tanween (the noon with sukun and doubled vowels) are marked with different colors for each of their four outcomes: izhar (clear pronunciation), idgham (merging), iqlab (changing noon to meem), and ikhfa (hiding the noon sound). Similarly, the rules for the meem sakinah are clearly marked for izhar, idgham shafawi, and ikhfa shafawi. The rules of madd (elongation) are indicated with separate colors for madd tabii (natural elongation), madd wajib muthaqqal and madd wajib mukhaffaf (obligatory elongation), madd muttasil (connected elongation), madd munfasil (separated elongation), and madd aarid lil-sukun (temporary elongation caused by a pause). Additionally, the rules of qalqalah (echoing sound for the qaf, taa, baa, jeem, and dal), the ghunnah (nasalization), and the rules for the letter laam in the word Allah are all indicated with their respective colors.

The physical production of this Quran edition maintains the highest standards of quality. The Arabic text is printed in a clear, large, and well-spaced Uthmanic script that is easy to read and reduces eye strain during extended recitation sessions. The pages are made from high-quality, opaque paper that prevents show-through from the reverse side, and the binding is designed for durability to withstand daily use. The color coding is applied with precision so that it enhances readability without creating visual clutter or distraction. This edition is particularly beneficial for students who are learning tajweed for the first time, as the visual cues serve as a constant reminder of the rules and help build correct recitation habits. It is also valuable for more advanced reciters who want to verify their application of specific rules, for teachers of Quran recitation who use it as a teaching tool, and for Huffaz (those who have memorized the Quran) who wish to review and perfect their tajweed. The color-coded Tajweed Quran has become one of the most popular formats for Quran publication in the contemporary Muslim world and is used extensively in homes, mosques, madrasahs, and Islamic schools.`,
    metaDescription: "Tajweed Quran Color Coded helps readers apply recitation rules. Color-coded letters indicate madd, ghunnah, qalqalah, and other tajweed rules."
